        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 12 at 3:48PM EDT by NWS Indianapolis IN</headline>
        <description>At 348 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 7
miles northeast of Columbus, moving northeast at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Columbus, Hope, Flat Rock, Milford, Geneva, Hartsville, Clifford,
Newbern, Burney, and Taylorsville.

This includes Interstate 65 near mile marker 77.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
